               <p>520. <persName id="def1-520-18560514" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-520-18560514" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-520-18560514" type="age" value="36"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-520-18560514" type="surname" value="TRUEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-520-18560514" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY TRUEMAN</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-520-18560514" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-520-18560514" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-520-18560514" type="surname" value="HOUGH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-520-18560514" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">BENJAMIN HOUGH</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18560514-520-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18560514-520-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18560514-520-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>, stealing 10 cwt. of coals, value 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18560514-name-358" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-358" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-358" type="surname" value="FREEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-358" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18560514-520-offence-1 t18560514-name-358"></join>Thomas Freeman</persName>, their masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ORRIDGE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-359" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-359" type="surname" value="CHANNON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-359" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES CHANNON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to Mr. Thomas Freeman, of Blackfrian<lb></lb>wharf, Blackfriars—the prisoners were in his employ. On 3rd May I sent them with ten tons of coals to Mr. Wheeler, in Hyde-park-gardens, seven tons first and then three tons—Trueman, the carman, and Hough, his <hi rend="italic">trouncer</hi>, left the yard with a waggon, with three tons, about a quarter past 9 o'clock—I saw them go—there were thirty sacks in the waggon, con<lb></lb>taining each two cwt, or 224lbs. of coals—from what I heard afterwards the prisoners were given into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALFE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you see the coals put into the waggon? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I saw them in the waggon when they went out, and I counted the sacks in the waggon—there were ten sacks down the side, and three across, which made thirty—I gave the ticket for that number—Trueman had been with us about two years—during that time he has borne a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-360" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-360" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-360" type="surname" value="GURR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-360" type="given" value="ALFRED JAMES"></interp>ALFRED JAMES GURR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am butler to Mrs. Wheeler, of Hyde-paik-gardens. On 3rd May some coals were brought to our house—my mistress opened the window, and asked Trueman, the carman, if he had three tons of coals, he said, "Yes"—she asked if he had thirty sacks, he said, "Yes"—my mistress and I watched them, and on shooting two or three sacks, an empty sack turned up—it was taken out by Trueman, and put on the others—in the course of shooting a few more, four more empty sacks turned up, and were put on the others—twenty-five full sacks were shot, and five empty sacks were placed by the side of them—Mrs. Wheeler opened the window, and said, "You have not brought thirty sacks of coals"—Trueman said, "Yes, I have"—she said, "You have not, twenty-five sacks were full, and five were empty"—Hough came into the house afterwards—I told him it was a serious affair, and Mrs. Wheeler would have to go to Mr. Freeman</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185605140259"></xptr>
               <p>about it—there were only twenty-five sacks of coals—he said he knew nothing of it—Mrs. Wheeler went down to Mr. Freeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examimd. Q.</hi> Did not Hough say, if it were not right, if you would give him the ticket, he would have it made right at the office? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, he asked me for the ticket, and I told him I could not give it him, on account of the coals not being the proper quantity.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-361" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-361" type="surname" value="TRIM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-361" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS TRIM</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 69). I took Trueman into custody, on Saturday, 3rd May, about half past 3 o'clock in the afternoon.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-362" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-362" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-362" type="surname" value="BUCKTHORPE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-362" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHABLES BUCKTHORPE</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 318) I took Hough into custody on Saturday evening, 3rd May—I told him the charge—he said he was not responsible for it, he was servant to the carman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALFE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">ALFRED JAMES GURR</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did Trueman ask you to have the coals weighed? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> That was not said in my hearing—I asked my mistress, and she said she did not hear it—I could not say whether there was a weighing machine in the waggon—my mistress and I were both standing at the window, which was open.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">TRUEMAN</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18560514-520-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
